Article   Type:BFN 

  [Editorial Report] The following is a compilation of 
reports on economic activities in Bolivia monitored through 10 
March. 
  National Treasury Under Secretary Edgar Saravia reported 
that 
the Treasury expects to collect 3.6 billion bolivianos for the 
1994 national budget. The projected revenues are higher than 
those collected last year. (La Paz LA RAZON in Spanish 19 Feb 94 
p B2) 
  Bolivian Central Bank, BCB, President Fernando Candia stated 
that this year the BCB will be able to grant $100 million to 
$120 million in credits to the private sector because of the 
level of its international reserves, which totals $330 million. 
(La Paz LA RAZON in Spanish 24 Feb 94 p A16) 
  Oil production in the tropical zone of Chapare, Cochabamba 
Department, rose to 7,000 barrels per day. It accounts for 24.3 
percent of the total production, after Santa Cruz Department. 
(La Paz PRESENCIA in Spanish 27 Feb 94 p 7) 
  The economic growth in the year's first two months was slow 
compared with the goals projected for this period. The consumer 
price index increased 0.83 percent in January, which is "low" 
compared with those registered in the same month of the last 
three years. (Cochabamba LOS TIEMPOS in Spanish 27 Feb 94 p A11) 

